  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/langfengq--verl-agent",
  "meta": {
    "title": "News",
    "description": "verl-agent is an extension of veRL, designed for training LLM/VLM agents via RL. verl-agent is also the official code for paper \"Group-in-Group Policy Optimization for LLM Agent Training\"",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-09T11:17:50.443Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-09T11:17:50.443Z",
    "keywords": [
      "agent-framework",
      "deepseek-r1",
      "gigpo",
      "grpo",
      "large-language-models",
      "llm-agents",
      "llm-training",
      "reinforcement-learning"
    ],
    "license": "Apache-2.0"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "| Feature Category | Supported Capabilities|\n| - | - |\n| **Interaction**          | ✅ Multi-turn Agent-Environment interaction<br>✅ Step-wise interaction<br>✅ Scalable for long-horizon tasks |\n| **Memory**               | ✅ Fully customizable memory module<br>✅ Flexible history management|\n| **Input Flexibility**    | ✅ Fully customizable per-step input structures |\n| **Execution**            | ✅ Parallelized Gym environments<br>✅ Group environments support (for group-based RL)|\n| **Model Support**        | ✅ Qwen3<br>✅ Qwen3-VL<br>✅ Qwen2.5<br>✅ Qwen2.5-VL<br>✅ LLaMA3.2<br>and more |\n| **Modality**             | ✅ Text-only<br>✅ Text + Image (multi-modal) |\n| **Lightweight Training** | ✅ Supports LoRA training |\n| **Environments**         | ✅ ALFWorld<br>✅ WebShop<br> ✅ Search (Tool Calling)<br> ✅ Sokoban<br>✅ Gym Cards<br>✅ AppWorld |\n| **RL Algorithms**        | ✅ GiGPO<br>✅ GRPO<br>✅ PPO<br>✅ DAPO<br>✅ GSPO<br>✅ RLOO<br>✅ REINFORCE++<br>✅ Dynamic sampling & clip-higher supported <br> and more |\n| **Prompt-based Agent**   | ✅ GPT-4o prompt-based agent  |",
    "context": "- [2026.02] `HGPO` accepted at [ICLR 2026](https://iclr.cc/)! 🎉🎉🎉 [[Paper](https://openreview.net/forum?id=T8Dev99qnz)] [[Code](https://github.com/langfengQ/verl-agent/tree/master/recipe/hgpo)]\n- [2026.02] 🔥 We open-source [Dr. MAS](https://github.com/langfengQ/DrMAS), which supports stable end-to-end RL post-training of **multi-agent LLM systems**! [[Paper](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.08847)] [[Code](https://github.com/langfengQ/DrMAS)]\n- [2025.12] `Qwen3-VL` is supported! See example [here](./examples/gigpo_trainer/run_sokoban_qwen3vl.sh).\n- [2025.09] `GiGPO` is now supported by [ROLL](https://github.com/alibaba/ROLL)! [[Document](https://alibaba.github.io/ROLL/docs/English/UserGuide/agentic/agentic_GiGPO)] [[Train Curves](https://github.com/alibaba/ROLL/issues/173#issuecomment-3332106534)].\n- [2025.09] `verl-agent`-style training pipeline is now supported by [OpenManus-RL](https://github.com/OpenManus/OpenManus-RL)!\n- [2025.09] [GiGPO](https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.10978) accepted at [NeurIPS 2025](https://neurips.cc/)! 🎉🎉🎉\n- [2025.08] Add **Search-R1 experiments** and **similarity-based GiGPO**! Check out GiGPO's superior performance in Search-R1 experiments [here](#results).\n- [2025.07] `GiGPO` & `verl-agent` talks at [Agent for SWE meetup](https://lu.ma/e498qhsi) by LF AI & Data Singapore on 7/11.\n- [2025.07] Add modular memory manager. See [here](./agent_system/memory).\n- [2025.06] ***Major update***: Merge all features from the latest [veRL](https://github.com/volcengine/verl). For example, `verl-agent` now supports Qwen3, LoRA, REINFORCE++, and more. Feel free to explore!\n- [2025.05] Code released and paper on `GiGPO` released.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
